# EC2 Lab 7 — Logging & Basic Visibility

## 🎯 Objective
To investigate server activity using system logs and command history to understand who accessed the instance and what actions were performed.

## 🧪 Scenario
A server may have been accessed. Logs are used to determine login activity and commands executed.

## ☁️ AWS Services Used
- EC2 (Linux instance)

## 🔍 Focus
- Authentication logs
- Command history
- Basic incident visibility

## 🧠 Key Idea
Logs provide evidence of activity on a system and are essential for detecting unauthorized access.
